Scenario: Simulate a sample organization called 'Demo Corp'

Part 1 - Create Sample 'Org Chart'

1. Open Active Directory Users and Computers (ADUC)
2. Right click the domain name (ad.lab)
3. Select New > Organization Unit > Name it DemoCorp_Root
4. Right click the new DemoCorp_Root folder and create four sub-OUs:
  - Admin_Department (for IT Staff)
  - General_Staff (for HR, Sales)
  - Workstations (for Computers
  - Groups

Part 2 - Create the Groups
  1. Right click the Groups OU > New > Group
    - Group Name: G_HR_Staff
    - Scope: Global / Type: Security
  2. Right cligh the Groups OU > New > Group
    - Group Name: G_IT_Admins
    - Scope: Global / Type: Security


Part 3 - Create the Users
  - I will use two contrasting users; one with admin power(Admin) and one who is restricted (Staff)

1. Create a Restricted User
  - Right click General_Staff OU > New > User
    - First Name: John 
    - Last Name: HR
    - User login: jhr@ad.lab
    - Password: Password123
  - Add to Group:
    - Right-click John HR > Properties > Member Of tab > Add > Type G_HR_Staff > OK.

2. Create an Admin 
  - Right click Admin_Department OU > New > User
    - First Name:  Jeff
    - Last Name: Admin
    - User login: jadmin@ad.lab
    -Password: Password123
  - Add to Group:
    - Right-click Jeff Admin > Properties > Member Of tab > Add > Type G_HR_Staff > OK  (For organizational tracking)  
    - Right click Jeff Admin > Properties > Member of tab > Add > Type Domain Admins  > OK  (For real admin priviledges)
